content: Read this before they erase it again. Last Telstra day we transferred 3 mobile phones from other carriers and 1 mobile broadband service to Telstra. We got a special rate for the 1st year or we wouldn't have agreed. Yet in the last day we've been informed that none of those rates will be honoured and instead we'll be charged more than what was full price as all prices went up on July 1. We were told we'd have 5G reception indoors by their coverage map. We have 1 bar of 3G outside if we're lucky. We were assured by the Eli who signed us up that my partner @lizhamdotcom could pay for her 2 services and I for my 2 yet we'd have a pool of data for all 4 to share as we'd have full authority on each other's accounts. What actually instead is that 500+ messages over 2 months to a revolving door of largely clueless support staff via your broken app has only today yielded a concession that we were promised something that could never be delivered. If we want to pool our data we have to fill out an 11 page change of ownership form and split all our bills off our own bat forever. When I finally reached an international complaints overseer a month ago she could not explain why the female half of our couple would only be granted limited authority for six months whilst I had full authority instantly. She said she would keep our case open yet closed it on the sly overnight. I now have to seek redress via the Ombudsman. Oh and we waited 4 hours for the follow-up appointment of a postponed-without-explanation visit by your techs to connect a landline (that was already a Telstra line under the last tenant and still had a dial tone, so why we have to be present for a physical visit Â god knows). Despite us honouring this set time for our second 'commencement day' by taking all of it off work to be here you neither turned up nor had the courtesy to call and say you wouldn't. We spent over an hour on hold to be told your own people have no idea why this visit never happened. They never do really. My case manager cannot even call or directly email me. A 'system limitation'. You are a telecommunications company that neither communicates nor provides the services you sell. Buyers beware!

content: @npbevo Hey there. 5G doesn't inherently use more data than 4G. It's essentially a more advanced version of the current mobile networks we use with technology that allows for faster speeds, lower latency and greater capacity. With this said, it's generally assumed that as we start to use 5G, we will naturally start to consume more data thanks to the attributes of 5G and how seamless it makes downloading large files, streaming content in Ultra HD and connecting multiple devices at once. For this reason, if you do plan to use 5G, we recommend making sure you optimise your phone settings so you can make the most of the mobile data included in your plan. â€“Taylor
